description.narrative: UNICEF took a two-pronged approach to the ensuring the availability of primary health care for children and women and Syria. With 16 implementing partners, UNICEF delivered 1.5 million maternal and child health consultations. At the same time, critical supplies and training were provided to support the national health care system, including to combat the ongoing waves of COVID-19.;To reduce neonatal mortality; UNICEF supported the national Healthy Villages Programme to reach 4,633 mothers and 2,350 newborns through 12,746 home visits by female community volunteers, and expanded the Every Newborn Action Plan network to include two additional hospitals. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
